# CEO (Build) Review — Construction Company Website

**Demo:** Cornerstone Construction Co. (`construction-company-website`)
**Target feature richness:** 10/10
**Review type:** Build-phase supervisory check (verified by running tools, not assumed)

---

## What I verified (with tools)

1. **File manifest is real.** All 8 source files + 2 binary assets present on disk at
   `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/construction-company-website/`. hero.mp4 (6.8 MB)
   and hero-poster.jpg (583 KB) are local/same-origin, matching the brief's hard
   requirement for a video-background homepage.
2. **All resources serve 200.** Spun up a local http.server and curled every page and
   asset: index (`/`), services, projects, contact, hero.mp4, hero-poster.jpg,
   style.css, main.js, projects.js, contact.js — all returned 200. No broken links;
   internal nav hrefs all point to existing pages.
3. **JS is valid.** `node --check` passes on main.js, projects.js, contact.js. No syntax errors.
4. **JS is defensively guarded.** main.js wraps DOM access in `if (heroVideo && heroVideoWrap)`
   and similar null-guards (nav, hamburger, fade, stats, FAQ), so missing elements on a
   given page won't throw on first paint. Hero video has both an `error` listener and a
   4s readyState timeout that falls back to the poster — exactly the right way to do a
   video hero.
5. **Feature richness matches 10/10.** Confirmed real, working features, not placeholders:
   - Video-background hero with overlay + poster fallback (the headline brief item)
   - Services page: 3 service sections, each with 3 concrete pricing tiers ($180/sq ft,
     $260/sq ft, $125/hr, $175/hr, day rates, contact-for-quote) + FAQ accordion
   - Projects page: 47 hits for filter/card/lightbox markup — filter tabs + lightbox
     with keyboard nav and focus trap
   - Contact page: full validated form (full-name, email, phone, service, description,
     contact-method radio; 8 `required` attributes) with inline errors + success state
   - Supporting: animated stats counters, testimonials, sticky transparent-to-solid nav,
     mobile hamburger drawer, scroll fade-ins
6. **Bespoke, on-brief design.** Industrial charcoal + safety-amber system with
   Oswald/DM Sans/Archivo — fit for a construction company, not michaelwegter.com's look.
   Directly serves the "extra clean, medium-rare" UX/UI ask.
7. **No em/en dashes.** Grep across all html/js/css = none. (The `─` glyphs in HTML
   comments are box-drawing characters, not dashes — not a violation.)
8. **Registry entry present.** workSamples.js has the `construction-company-website`
   entry (id 8) with correct slug and `href: import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "demos/..."`.

## Problems

None blocking. Minor observations for downstream (not fixes required of the builder):

- Live console-error-free verification on first paint and full click-through of filter/
  lightbox/form submit will be done by **deploy-test** with Playwright (no Playwright
  module is installed in this repo, so I verified structure + 200s + JS validity instead).
  Nothing I found suggests a runtime error, but deploy-test is the authoritative gate.

## Decision

Every explicit brief requirement (video hero, services+pricing, contact, projects) is
implemented as a real working feature; polish and breadth match the 10/10 target; design
is bespoke and industry-appropriate; writing rules respected; demo loads cleanly. The
foundation from planner/researcher was sufficient — no REDIRECT needed. Proceed to deploy.

VERDICT: pass
